This paper deals with the problem of photorealistic style transfer, which involves manipulating images to make them look more realistic while maintaining the style of a reference image. This falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV), which deals with the analysis and manipulation of visual data. Additionally, the paper uses mathematical techniques such as the Screened Poisson Equation, which falls under the category of graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.AI, and cs.LG.
